H0.text: Which country left the Commonwealthin 1972 and rejoined in 1989. Pakistan

H1.text: Which country left the Commonwealthin 1972 and rejoined in 1989. South Africa

H2.text: Which country left the Commonwealthin 1972 and rejoined in 1989. Fiji

H3.text: Which country left the Commonwealthin 1972 and rejoined in 1989. IROP

A4.text: South Africa withdrew from the Commonwealth in 1961 and rejoined in 1994.

A5.text: Pakistan left on 30 January 1972 in protest at the Commonwealth's recognition of breakaway Bangladesh, but rejoined on 2 August 1989.

A6.text: South Africa was re-admitted to the Commonwealth in 1994, following its first multiracial elections that year.
